# Copy to .dev.vars for local wrangler dev (not committed to git).
# Production values are set via Cloudflare dashboard or
# `wrangler secret put <NAME>`.

ENVIRONMENT=dev
API_CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000

# Resend API key — get yours at https://resend.com/api-keys
# Without this, POST /api/users/invite still succeeds but returns
# `emailSent: false` so the admin can copy the invite link manually.
RESEND_API_KEY=re_YOUR_KEY_HERE

# Supabase Storage credentials (storage-supabase-migration). Both required
# for /api/files (upload/download/delete) and the daily-backup cron to work
# locally. Without them, the file-asset routes return 503 and the cron
# logs "Supabase Storage credentials missing".
#
# SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF is the slug from your Supabase project URL — i.e.
# the segment before .supabase.co. NOT a secret on its own (it appears in
# every public Supabase URL) but lives here for parity with prod.
#
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY is the service_role key from Supabase dashboard ->
# Project Settings -> API. Treat it like a root password — it bypasses
# Row-Level Security and can read/write anything in the project. NEVER
# commit this file. NEVER ship it to the SPA bundle.
#
# Bucket "hookka-files" must exist in Supabase Storage before any upload
# works (Dashboard -> Storage -> New bucket -> Private). See
# docs/DR-RUNBOOK.md "Storage bootstrap" for the full one-time setup.
# SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF=your-project-ref
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=eyJ...service_role_key...

# Sentry / GlitchTip DSN for error reporting (Sprint 5).
# Frontend uses VITE_SENTRY_DSN (set in .env / .env.production at build
# time so the value is statically replaced into the bundle by Vite).
# Worker uses SENTRY_DSN (set via `wrangler secret put SENTRY_DSN` in
# prod, or via this file for local wrangler dev). Both are optional —
# leaving them unset disables monitoring with no other side effects.
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=https://abc123@sentry.example.com/1
# SENTRY_DSN=https://abc123@sentry.example.com/1
